node.title: Protesters disperse after months of occupation at Raglan Airfield
node.description: A group of protesters that had been gathered at the Raglan Airfield since January have left today.
node.content:
["A group of protesters that had been gathered at the Raglan Airfield since January have left today.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Richard Tindiller\n
", "They were opposing the construction of a fence surrounding the airfield.", "Waikato West area commander Inspector Will Loughrin said there was no trespass were given, nor any arrests made.", "\"Police had been in regular communication with the protest group in the past few weeks and had been working with them towards a peaceful resolution.\"", "Loughrin said he was pleased the occupation on the airfield was resolved without any significant issues."]
